effect

  • ‚óè 2+: Monsters your opponent controls lose 100 ATK/DEF for each face-up banished card.
  • ‚óè 4+: The first time each "Nauticorpse" card you control would be destroyed each turn, it is not destroyed.
  • ‚óè 6+: Once per turn: You can target 1 of your banished "Nauticorpse" cards; add it to your hand.
  • ‚óè 8+: Once per turn, when your opponent activates a card or effect (Quick Effect): You can negate the activation, and if you do, send that card to the GY.
  • ‚óè 10+: During your turn, this Ritual Summoned card is unaffected by the effects of monsters whose current ATK is less than half of this card's original ATK.

effect

  • This card can be used to Ritual Summon any "Undyne" Ritual Monster from your Deck or GY. You must also Tribute monsters from your hand or field, whose total DEF equals or exceeds the DEF of the Ritual Monster you Ritual Summon. If you use this effect, you cannot Special Summon for the rest of this turn, except "Undyne" monsters. You can shuffle this card from your GY into the Deck; add 1 "Undyne" card from your GY to your hand. You can only use this effect of "Undyne Calling" once per turn.

Undyne Empire

‚úÖ ‚ùå ü™ì üíº üóëÔ∏è
(was nothing)
‚û°Ô∏è
effect

  • "Undyne" card effects treat this card you control as a Normal Monster (Rock/WATER/Level 12/ATK 0/DEF 3000). Monsters your opponent controls lose 250 ATK/DEF for each "Undyne" card you control. If you did not draw by your card effect this turn: You can Tribute 1 other "Undyne" card from your hand or field; draw 2 cards. Once per turn, during the End Phase: You can Ritual Summon 1 "Undyne" Ritual Monster from your GY by Tributing 1 monster you control that does not have less DEF than it.

Undyne Pact

4441702 ⋅ DB ⋅ EXU

‚úÖ ‚ùå ü™ì üíº üóëÔ∏è
(was nothing)
‚û°Ô∏è
effect

  • This card can be used to Ritual Summon any number of "Undyne" Ritual Monsters. Send 1 other card from your hand or field and 1 monster from your Extra Deck to the GY, also after that, Ritual Summon any number of "Undyne" monsters whose total DEF is less than the DEF of that monster. You can target up to 2 other cards in your GY, including 1 "Undyne" card; shuffle them into the Deck, also add this card from your GY to your hand. You can only use this effect of "Undyne Pact" once per turn.

Undyne Guardian

‚úÖ ‚ùå ü™ì üíº üóëÔ∏è
(was nothing)
‚û°Ô∏è
effect

  • Tribute 1 "Undyne" card from your hand, or 1 monster you control, then Special Summon this card as an Effect Monster (Aqua/Water/Level 12/ATK 0/DEF 3000). (This card is also still a Trap.) If this card is in the Monster Zone (Quick Effect): You can send 1 "Undyne" Ritual Spell from your Deck to the GY; this effect becomes that Spell's effect when the card is activated. You can activate this card the turn it was Set. You can only use each effect of "Undyne Guardian" once per turn.
